Kazakhstan is open to dynamic civilizations and welcomes all those who respect and understand us. This is Kasakshtan. Therefore, May 29, 2019, we received the Chairman of the Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD), Angel Gurria was presented with the Ashgabat Manifest.

“Ashgabat Manifesto” is a new international legal principle for organizing a global economy, written to support and highlight the contribution of innovations, high technologies and entrepreneurship to global sustainable development.

It aims at the creation of a global technological development model that is socially oriented, and implementation of its top selected goals into practice through the development of interactive communication between governments, business, universities, non-profit organizations and international financial organizations of project implementation.

The Manifesto is based on the global community development, understanding policy making as “necessary ability to look at the markets”. One more has called the Manifesto “a set of principles on which the progress of the digital era depends”.
